      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 1895158715556237656, guid: fbbd29b5a230d9a4f9c6aa4c58bb7bdb, type: 3}
      propertyPath: steps.Array.data[3].stepType
      value: 3
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 1895158715556237656, guid: fbbd29b5a230d9a4f9c6aa4c58bb7bdb, type: 3}
      propertyPath: steps.Array.data[4].stepName
      value: Congrats!
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 1895158715556237656, guid: fbbd29b5a230d9a4f9c6aa4c58bb7bdb, type: 3}
      propertyPath: steps.Array.data[4].stepType
      value: 3
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 1895158715556237656, guid: fbbd29b5a230d9a4f9c6aa4c58bb7bdb, type: 3}
      propertyPath: steps.Array.data[0].description
      value: 'Find the laptop and  hover your mouse cursor to the laptop keyboard
        there are Ui''s that helps you to identify these parts and press E, you''ll
        see that it will now detached itself to the rest of the laptop



'
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 1895158715556237656, guid: fbbd29b5a230d9a4f9c6aa4c58bb7bdb, type: 3}
      propertyPath: steps.Array.data[1].description
      value: Try to hold left mouse button to the detached keyboard and drag it around
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 1895158715556237656, guid: fbbd29b5a230d9a4f9c6aa4c58bb7bdb, type: 3}
      propertyPath: steps.Array.data[2].description
      value: "Now, detached all the parts, keep in mind that the detachment have
        a dependency in which you must first remove before you may able to detached
        the planned laptop part, you'll see that the letter \"E\" will show on the
        parts that you are able to remove \n\n"
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 1895158715556237656, guid: fbbd29b5a230d9a4f9c6aa4c58bb7bdb, type: 3}
      propertyPath: steps.Array.data[3].description
      value: Upon finishing up the detached of all parts, try to hold onto a part
        and move it close to the laptop panels and when you see a preview of the
        part that you are holding, let go of the left mouse button and it will snap
        in place
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 1895158715556237656, guid: fbbd29b5a230d9a4f9c6aa4c58bb7bdb, type: 3}
      propertyPath: steps.Array.data[4].description
      value: Congratulations.. you finished the tutorial, press the ESC button for
        the dropdown Ui and you may exit the scene
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
